Title: Invoking Podam on a POJO with a circular constructor (e.g. java.net.URL) leads to a null POJO
Invoking Podam on a POJO with a private, no arguments constructor, should return a non null POJO
Invoking Podam on a POJO with both circular and non circular constructors (e.g. javax.activation.DataHandler) should lead to a non empty POJO
Invoking Podam on an Abstract class should return a null pojo
Invoking Podam on an interface should return an empty POJO
Podam should assign exactly the values specified with the @PodamStrategyValue annotation
Podam should assign precise values and lengths when a String is annotated with @PodamStringValue
Podam should fill AttributeMetadata with the attribute name
Podam should fill Java native types
Podam should fill POJOs with non default constructors
Podam should fill POJOs with protected, non default constructors
Podam should fill POJOs with public, non default constructors
Podam should fill arrays with elements
Podam should fill embedded abstract classes if a concrete type has been specified
Podam should fill in Maps of the containing class type
Podam should fill in POJOs which have a circular dependency
Podam should fill in POJOs with Enums
Podam should fill in a POJO with basic jvm types
Podam should fill in lists of the containing class type
Podam should fill recursive POJOs correctly, including all their fields
Podam should fill recursive POJOs when invoking the factory population directly
Podam should fill values invoking children setters accepting a type different from the parent type
Podam should generate a non null POJO for Abstract types with a concrete type
Podam should handle POJOs with constructors that have one or more self references to the POJO class, provided the required constructor is annotated with @PodamConstructor
Podam should handle POJOs with no setters and collections in the constructor
Podam should handle POJOs with private constructors only
Podam should handle POJOs with self reference constructors but not default constructors without the need for the @PodamConstructor annotation
Podam should handle Singletons with parameters in the static method
Podam should handle basic inheritance scenarios
Podam should handle booleans correctly
Podam should handle both native and wrapped boolean values with @PodamBooleanValue annotation
Podam should handle both native and wrapped byte values with @PodamByteValue annotation
Podam should handle both native and wrapped char values with @PodamCharValue annotation
Podam should handle both native and wrapped double values with @PodamDoubleValue annotation
Podam should handle both native and wrapped float values with @PodamFloatValue annotation
Podam should handle both native and wrapped integer values with @PodamIntValue annotation
Podam should handle both native and wrapped long values with @PodamLongValue annotation
Podam should handle both native and wrapped short values with @PodamShortValue annotation
Podam should handle immutable POJOs annotated with @PodamConstructor
Podam should handle immutable POJOs with generified collections in the constructor
Podam should handle immutable Pojos with non generic collections
Podam should handle immutable non annotated POJOs
Podam should handle standard collections
Podam should not fill POJO's attributes annotated with @PodamExclude
Podam should throw an exception if a POJO contains invalid getters or setters
Podam should throw an exception if the @PodamByteValue annotation contains invalid characters
Podam should throw an exception if the @PodamDoubleValue annotation contains invalid characters
Podam should throw an exception if the @PodamFloatValue annotation contains invalid characters
Podam should throw an exception if the @PodamIntegerValue annotation contains invalid characters
Podam should throw an exception if the @PodamLongValue annotation contains invalid characters
Podam should throw an exception if the @PodamShortValue annotation contains invalid characters
Podam should throw an exception if the @PodamStrategyValue annotation contains the wrong strateg type
The @PodamCollection annotation should allow to set sizes on all collections and arrays
